---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro'
import Math from '../components/Math.astro'
import { sourceFile } from '../data/site'
---

<BaseLayout title="Poincaré–Einstein Geometry">
  <section class="page-intro">
    <div class="site-shell">
      <p class="eyebrow">Poincaré–Einstein Geometry</p>

      <h1>Compactification, normal form, Einstein data, and the ambient cone bridge.</h1>

      <p>
        The PE layer turns conformally compact bulk-and-boundary data into a
        formal interface for normal-form geometry, renormalization, and
        invariant applications.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="site-shell grid-2">
      <article class="card">
        <h3>Defining Functions</h3>

        <Math display tex="r>0,\qquad r=0\ \text{on}\ \partial X" />

        <Math display tex="\overline g=r^2g_+" />

        <p>
          Boundary defining functions compactify the PE metric. Geodesic
          defining functions additionally encode the normalized gradient
          condition required by Poincaré normal form.
        </p>

        <a
          class="source-link"
          href={sourceFile('ConformalCovariantOperators/Ambient/PE/DefiningFunction.lean')}
          target="_blank"
          rel="noreferrer"
        >
          Open DefiningFunction.lean ↗
        </a>
      </article>

      <article class="card">
        <h3>Poincaré Normal Form</h3>

        <Math display tex="g_+=r^{-2}(dr^2+h_r)" />

        <p>
          The formal PE normal-form package records the boundary metric
          <Math tex="h_0" />, the collar family <Math tex="h_r" />, and their
          compatibility with conformal infinity.
        </p>

        <a
          class="source-link"
          href={sourceFile('ConformalCovariantOperators/Ambient/PE/NormalForm.lean')}
          target="_blank"
          rel="noreferrer"
        >
          Open NormalForm.lean ↗
        </a>
      </article>

      <article class="card">
        <h3>Einstein Equation and Parity</h3>

        <Math display tex="\operatorname{Ric}(g_+)=-ng_+" />

        <Math display tex="h_r=h_0+h_2r^2+h_4r^4+\cdots" />

        <p>
          The implementation records the PE Einstein condition with formal
          even-expansion and trace-free obstruction certificates.
        </p>

        <a
          class="source-link"
          href={sourceFile('ConformalCovariantOperators/Ambient/PE/EinsteinEquation.lean')}
          target="_blank"
          rel="noreferrer"
        >
          Open EinsteinEquation.lean ↗
        </a>
      </article>

      <article class="card">
        <h3>Ambient–PE Bridge</h3>

        <Math display tex="\rho=-\frac{r^2}{2},\qquad s=rt" />

        <Math display tex="g_{\mathrm{ambient}}=-ds^2+s^2g_+" />

        <p>
          The bridge connects Fefferman–Graham normal-form data with PE
          geometry through the radial coordinate change and cone decomposition.
        </p>

        <a
          class="source-link"
          href={sourceFile('ConformalCovariantOperators/Ambient/PE/AmbientBridge.lean')}
          target="_blank"
          rel="noreferrer"
        >
          Open AmbientBridge.lean ↗
        </a>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>